// go.work — Multi-module workspace for the Orkestra monorepo.
//
// Two modules live here today:
//
//   - backend/                    github.com/orkestra/backend
//     The monolith + ai-service binary, all core modules, all addons, and
//     backend-internal infrastructure (config, database, middleware,
//     telemetry, error wrappers, etc.).
//
//   - backend/pkg/sdk/            github.com/orkestra-cc/orkestra-sdk
//     The public SDK contract — Module interface, ServiceRegistry,
//     ConfigService, iface, ctxauth, modulegate, capability, tenantrepo,
//     metrics. Self-contained: no imports of any backend internal/
//     package. Phase 4 publishes this to its own GitHub repo at
//     orkestra-cc/orkestra-sdk; until then the workspace + a `replace`
//     directive in backend/go.mod bind it locally.
//
// Both `cd backend && go build ./...` and `cd backend/pkg/sdk && go test ./...`
// resolve correctly because the workspace knows where each module lives.
// CI runs make targets from the repo root, so go.work is always picked up.

go 1.25.10

use (
	./backend
	./backend/pkg/sdk
	./backend/internal/addons/documents
)
